profile_description:Colombia Huila Betania Chiloso Washed COE\vVariety: Chiloso | Altitude: 1800-1900m\vMoisture: 12% (nominal), est. ~10-10.5% (aged 8mo)\vDensity: Unknown (est. 840-870g/L)\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 3 - V2 curve format fix + parameter tuning\v\vV2 FAILURE (log0100): roast_profile format error caused\vcurve truncation and straight-line ramp. Roast ended at\v283s with only 3.3% weight loss. UNUSABLE.\v\vV3 strategy: restore F-WSH 1500-2200 template curve\v(proven working in V1/log0099), adjust parameters only:\v1. expect_fc: 204->200C (V1 actual FC was 197C)\v2. recommended_level: 2.0->2.5 (aged bean needs more dev)\v3. preheat: 790->810W (V1 mid-section was slightly fast)\v\vThese parameter changes achieve the V2 goals safely:\v- Lower expect_fc slows PID in FC zone -> extends dev\v- Higher Level adds 2C endpoint -> more Maillard products\v- Higher preheat compensates for longer time in mid-zone\v\vExpected improvements vs V1 (log0099):\v  Dev ratio: 16.2% -> 18-20% (target)\v  End temp: 203.4C -> ~205-206C\v  Total time: 369s -> ~390-410s\v  Maillard: more time at higher endpoint\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Light Clean: Level 1.5 (~202C)\v  Light Balanced: Level 2.0 (~204C)\v  Sweet Developed: Level 2.5 (~206C) <- Target\v  Medium Light: Level 3.0 (~208C)\v\vC40 pour-over grind: 24-28 clicks\vResting period: 5-7 days minimum\v
